There's a TypeScript error in main.ts at line 452. Let me see what's there.Looking at main.ts line 449-452:
```typescript
app.on('window-all-closed', (e: Event) => {
    e.preventDefault();
});```

The error says "Argument of type '(e: Event) => void' is not assignable to parameter of type '() => void'". This is a TypeScript type mismatch - the `window-all-closed` event handler doesn't receive an event argument in Electron 33's type definitions.In Electron 28, `window-all-closed` might have accepted an Event parameter, but in Electron 33's type definitions, the handler doesn't take any parameters.The fix: either remove the `(e: Event)` parameter, or use a different approach to prevent quitting.Actually, looking at the Electron documentation, `window-all-closed` doesn't pass any event to the listener. The way to prevent quitting is to just not call `app.quit()`. 

So I need to remove the event parameter and just leave the handler empty to keep the app running in the system tray instead of quitting.

